title: For Sale:  Winchester 1892
postcontent: Winchester 1892 rifle shown. Caliber is .38-40 Winchester. The 1892 is a lever action rifle with a 24" round barrel and a full length magazine tube. The S/N is 348618 indicating that it was made in 1905. The overall condition is good. The rifle retains most of a blued finish, it is hard for me to tell if it is original. The markings are nice and sharp, the metal does not appear to have been buffed at all. The finish shows some high edge wear, some dings and light scratching. The plain walnut forearm and matching butt stock are in good condition, there is a slight crack where the butt meets the frame on the right side. One of the upper tang screws has been replaced by what looks like an 1873 lever lock. The smooth metal crescent butt plate is worn with a grayish brown patina. The bore is very good, clean and shiny for the most part. The action seems to function fine. Overall, a very nice Winchester 1892 rifle that will make a fine shooter. I can ship.
